----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPalette.ManuallyCreate
Summary
  Indicates that the current frame must be taken into account to manually create the palette.
Description
  Use this call from a frame callback and set the flag to true to indicate that the current frame
  must be considered when creating the palette. Continue calling this method with flag set to true as
  long as you need it. Then call it again with flag set to false, to finalize the palette and pass it
  to the capture driver that will now use it.
Parameters
  Flag     - True to continue the creation, false to stop the creation.
  nbColors - Maximum number of colors in the palette.
Return value
  True if the call was successful.
See Also
  TJvPalette.AutoCreate, TJvPalette.Load, TJvPalette.PasteFromClipboard, TJvPalette.Save

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPalette.Load
Summary
  Loads the palette from a file.
Description
  Tries to load the palette from the given file.
Parameters
  FileName - The name of the file containing the palette to load.
Return value
  True if the palette was loaded successfully, false otherwise.
See Also
  TJvPalette.AutoCreate, TJvPalette.ManuallyCreate, TJvPalette.PasteFromClipboard, TJvPalette.Save

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPalette.AutoCreate
Summary
  Automatically create the best palette.
Description
  The best possible palette will be created for a maximum number of nbColors. It will be computed from
  the first nbFrames frames in the video stream.
Parameters
  nbFrames - The number of frames to consider for the creation of the palette.
  nbColors - The maximum number of colors the palette can contain.
Return value
  True if the palette was successfully created
See Also
  TJvPalette.Load, TJvPalette.ManuallyCreate, TJvPalette.PasteFromClipboard

