@@TJvCaptureSettings.Update
Summary
  Updates the properties of the object according to the values from the TJvAVICapture object.
Description
  This ensures synchronization between the object and the underlying system object. You shouldn't
  have to call this method directly.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.Apply

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.Yield
Summary
  Controls whether or not the capture will block the calling thread.
Description
  If set to true, when the capture starts, a separate thread is created allowing the thread launching
  the capture to continue. Reentrance issues must then be considered to avoid the user to launch
  twice the capture, for instance.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.StepCaptureAverageFrames
Summary
  Controls the number of frames to be sampled to calculate a frame when using step capture.
Description
  This is only taken into account when doing step capture. The given number of frames will be
  captured and averaged to generate the resulting frame.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.StepCapture2x

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.TimeLimit
Summary
  The time limit in seconds for the capture.
Description
  This is only taken into account if LimitEnabled is true.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.LimitEnabled

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.StepCapture2x
Summary
  Controls whether or not to capture at twice the size of the original stream.
Description
  If set to true, the resulting stream will have its width and height doubled at the expense of
  processing power.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.StepCaptureAverageFrames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.PercentDropForError
Summary
  The percentage of frames dropped above which the capture is aborted in error.
Description
  When capturing a video stream, the processing load may not allow to capture every frame sent by the
  video device. Those frames are then dropped. If the ratio of dropped frames on captured frames is
  above this percentage, the capture is ended in error. This means that if you were grabbing in a
  file, that file will not be complete.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.NumVideoBuffer
Summary
  The number of video buffers to use.
Description
  This is a requested value and may not be respected. The higher the value, the less chances to miss
  on video data, but the higher the processing load and the memory usage.
  Note
  It seems that this value is not taken into account under Windows 32Bit.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.AudioBufferSize, TJvCaptureSettings.NumAudioBuffer

