@@TJvCaptureSettings.LimitEnabled
Summary
  Controls whether or not the time limit is enabled.
Description
  If set to true, the capture time limit is enabled.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.AbortLeftMouse, TJvCaptureSettings.AbortRightMouse, TJvCaptureSettings.KeyAbort,
  TJvCaptureSettings.TimeLimit

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.KeyAbort
Summary
  The virtual key that will abort the capture session if pressed.
Description
  Set this value to a virtual key that will cancel the capture session if pressed. This defaults to
  the
  Esc key. You should use the TJvVirtualKeySelectionFrame selection frame (in
  JvVirtualKeySelectionFrame.pas) to allow your user to choose a virtual key, while being sure the
  value returned is correct.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.AbortLeftMouse, TJvCaptureSettings.AbortRightMouse,
  TJvCaptureSettings.LimitEnabled, TJvCaptureSettings.TimeLimit

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.FrameDelay
Summary
  The requested delay between two frames in microsecond.
Description
  This is only a requested number and may not be respected by the capture system if the processing
  load is too high.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.FPS

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.FPS
Summary
  The requested number of Frames Per Second.
Description
  This is only a requested number and may not be respected by the capture system if the processing
  load is too high.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.FrameDelay

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.ConfirmCapture
Summary
  Controls whether or not to confirm the capture.
Description
  If set to true, a message box will be shown to the user when you start the capture, allowing to
  continue or cancel the capture session.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.CaptureAudio
Summary
  Controls whether or not to capture audio.
Description
  If set to true, the audio data will be captured and saved in the stream.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.AudioBufferSize, TJvCaptureSettings.AudioMaster

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.AudioMaster
Summary
  Controls if the Audio stream is the master timer.
Description
  If set to true, the duration of the video stream will be forced to match the audio stream duration.
  This is generally not a good idea as it may introduce variations in the video frame rate.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.AudioBufferSize, TJvCaptureSettings.CaptureAudio

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.AudioBufferSize
Summary
  The size in bytes of each audio buffer.
Description
  If left at the default value of 0, the size of each audio buffer will be the maximum of 10 kbytes
  and 0.5 seconds of audio data.
See Also
  TJvCaptureSettings.AudioMaster, TJvCaptureSettings.CaptureAudio

