Return value
  True if the session started successfully.
See Also
  TJvAVICapture.CaptureFrame, TJvAVICapture.SingleFrameCapturing

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAVICapture.StartPreview
Summary
  Starts live preview.
Description
  Starts previewing the video stream using GDI calls. This is highly CPU intensive but is sure to
  work on any system. You should first try to use Overlaying and if that doesn't work, fallback to
  this method.
Return value
  True if live preview started successfully.
See Also
  TJvAVICapture.Overlaying, TJvAVICapture.Previewing, TJvAVICapture.StartOverlay,
  TJvAVICapture.StopOverlay, TJvAVICapture.StopPreview

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAVICapture.StartOverlay
Summary
  Starts overlay rendering.
Description
  If the driver supports it, this is the preferred method for doing live previewing.
Return value
  True if the overlay rendering started successfully.
See Also
  TJvAVICapture.DriverCaps, TJvAVICapture.Overlaying, TJvAVICapture.Previewing,
  TJvAVICapture.StartPreview, TJvAVICapture.StopOverlay

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
