@@TJvAVICapture.OnYield
Summary
  The event triggered when the driver is yielding.
Description
  This a good place to put a call to Application.ProcessMessages even if you must ensure that this
  call doesn't take too long as the capture is suspended until the end of this event. This event will
  only be triggered if ueYield is in UsedEvents.
Parameters
  Sender - The TJvAVICapture component triggering the event.
See Also
  TJvAVICapture.UsedEvents

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAVICapture.OnWaveStream
Summary
  The event triggered when an audio buffer is ready, during streaming capture.
Description
  This event is triggered just before the buffer is written do disk, leaving you the opportunity to
  modify it if needed. This event will only be triggered if ueAudioStream is in UsedEvents.
Parameters
  Sender  - The TJvAVICapture component triggering the event.
  waveHdr - The audio header describing the buffer.
See Also
  TJvAVICapture.UsedEvents

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAVICapture.OnVideoStream
Summary
  The event triggered when a frame is ready, in a streaming capture session.
Description
  This event is triggered just before the frame is written to disk. So if you make any changes to the
  frame in this event, they will be written to disk. This event will only be triggered if
  ueVideoStream is in UsedEvents.
Parameters
  Sender   - The TJvAVICapture component triggering the event.
  videoHdr - A PJvVideoHdr structure containing informations about the frame.
See Also
  TJvAVICapture.UsedEvents

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAVICapture.OnFrame
Summary
  The event triggered when a frame is ready, in a non streaming capture session.
Description
