----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.SamplesPerSec
Summary
  Number of samples per second in the audio stream.
Description
  If FormatTag is set to WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, then usual values for SamplesPerSec are 8000, 11025, 22050,
  44100 as they specify the frequency in Hertz at which the sampling will be done.
See Also
  TJvAudioFormat.FillWaveFormatEx, TJvAudioFormat.FormatTag

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.FormatTag
Summary
  The tag identifying the audio format used.
Description
  This value identifies the audio format used. If set to WAVE_FORMAT_PCM it will provoke a different
  behavior in FillWaveFormatEx.
See Also
  TJvAudioFormat.FillWaveFormatEx

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.ExtraSize
Summary
  Size of the Extra buffer in bytes.
Description
  Size of the Extra buffer in bytes.
See Also
  TJvAudioFormat.Extra, TJvAudioFormat.FillWaveFormatEx

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.FillWaveFormatEx
Summary
  Fills a WAVEFORMATEX structure with the informations contained in the properties.
Description
  The WAVEFORMATEX structure will be filled with the required informations from the properties of the
  TJvAudioFormat object. If the FormatTag is WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, the values will be set to comply with
  the recommendations for this format. If set to another value, the properties will be copied
  straight into the structure without any check.
Parameters
  wfex - The WAVEFORMATEX structure to be filled.
See Also
  TJvAudioFormat.FormatTag

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.Channels
Summary
  Number of channels in the audio stream.
Description
  1 for mono, 2 for stereo.
See Also
  TJvAudioFormat.FillWaveFormatEx, TJvAudioFormat.FormatTag

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.Extra
Summary
  Some extra data required by the format indicated by FormatTag.
Description
  If FormatTag is equal to WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, then the value of Extra is ignored. Please refer to the
  provider of the audio format you want to use for information on the data to put in this buffer.
See Also
  TJvAudioFormat.FillWaveFormatEx, TJvAudioFormat.FormatTag

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.BitsPerSample
Summary
  The number of bits per sample in the audio format.
Description
  If FormatTag is set to WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, this value must be either 8 or 16.
See Also
  TJvAudioFormat.FillWaveFormatEx, TJvAudioFormat.FormatTag

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.BlockAlign
Summary
  Block alignment in Bytes.
Description
  This value depends on the value of FormatTag. If it is equal to WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, then the value of
  BlockAlign will be ignored and computed according to.
  
  <CODE>
     BlockAlign := (Channels * BitsPerSample) div 8 </CODE>
See Also
  TJvAudioFormat.BitsPerSample, TJvAudioFormat.Channels, TJvAudioFormat.FillWaveFormatEx,
  TJvAudioFormat.FormatTag

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.AvgBytesPerSec
Summary
  The average number of bytes per second in the audio stream.
Description
  This value must be calculated according to the provider of the audio format you want to use and
  that you indicated by setting the value of FormatTag. Please note that if FormatTag is equal to
  WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, the value of AvgBytesPerSec will be ignored and will be computed according to the
  recommendation for this format:
  
  <CODE>
     AvgBytesPerSec := SamplesPerSec * ((Channels * BitsPerSample) div 8) </CODE>
See Also
  TJvAudioFormat.BitsPerSample, TJvAudioFormat.Channels, TJvAudioFormat.FillWaveFormatEx,
  TJvAudioFormat.FormatTag, TJvAudioFormat.SamplesPerSec

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.Apply
Summary
  Tries to apply the values in the properties of the audio format object to the video stream to which
  this audio format is linked to.
Description
  When you make modifications to the values of the properties, you must call this function or your
  changes will be ignored when you start grabbing. The most common and simple audio format to use is
  WAVE_FORMAT_PCM as it is always available on all machines but it doesn't provide any compression.
Return value
  True if the values were correct and successfully applied, false otherwise.

